@JDWarner @blink1073 here's @luispedro rightly ranting against forward-compatibility-breaking API changes:

https://metarabbit.wordpress.com/2013/09/23/to-reproduce-the-paper-you-cannot-use-the-code-we-used-for-the-paper/#id1

Just don't do it. This slows development down but that's what needs to happen when you become a widely-used project with a published paper and API.

