you can do this:
```
def _to_exclude(props, conditions=None):
    for condition in conditions or []:

```
server {
  server_name X;
  listen A;
  listen B;
  listen 443 ssl;
}

server {
  server_name Y;
  listen B;
  listen C;
}
```

This is the setup you're talking about?

A thing to note here is that `vhost.ssl` implies that at least one address in the server block is listening sslishly.

Whether or not address B (and therefore vhost Y) gets marked as `ssl` depends on what B is. If B is equivalent to `*:80`, it will get correctly marked as ssl, and pass that on to vhost Y. C will only be marked as `ssl` if it is also equivalent to B.
